  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed roof extension would be an inappropriate addition to the building by virtue of it interrupting a generally unbroken roof line of this part of the terrace when viewed from public and private areas. In addition, the materials and positioning of the windows and doors do not respect the character and appearance of the building and wider East Canonbury Conservation Area. This is contrary to policies D4, D11, D22, D24 and D25 of the Islington Unitary Development Plan (2002), policy CS9 of the Core Strategy (2011), the Conservation Area Design Guidelines (2002) and section 2.4.2 of the Islington Urban Design Guide 2006."
